Title: The Mission
Description: Hoss helps an army troop transport gold, but the troop’s former scout plans to steal it.
Short Description: A troop scout plans to steal gold.

Title: Feet of Clay
Description: The Cartwrights look after a young boy whose mother has just died, but the boy’s convict father has other ideas.
Short Description: A boy's convict father causes trouble for the Cartwrights

Title: Silent Thunder
Description: Little Joe teaches a deaf- mute mountain girl sign language, and mistakes his kindness for love.
Short Description: A deaf-mute girl falls for Little Joe.

Title: Day of Reckoning
Description: Ben gives an Indian couple some land to start a farm after they save his life, but a racist neighbor makes trouble.
Short Description: A racist couple causes trouble for an Indian couple

Title: San Francisco
Description: After a long cattle drive, Ben, Hoss and Little Joe visit San Francisco. Their ranch hands and Ben soon disappear.
Short Description: Ben and ranch hands diappear in San Francisco

Title: The Last Trophy
Description: Adam leads two old friends on a hunting trip, but they are taken captive by a renegade Indian band.
Short Description: Adam and his friends are captured during a hunting trip.

Title: The Hopefuls
Description: While in Virginia City Adam meets and fall in love with a Quaker girl. He accompanies her wagon train west but is faced with action that offends her morals.
Short Description: Adam falls in love with a Quaker woman in Virginia City

Title: Denver McKee
Description: The Cartwrights investigate a series of killings and robberies at nearby mines with the help of neighbor Denver McKee and his daughter.
Short Description: The Cartwrights and Denver McKee investigate murders in the mines.

Title: The Stranger
Description:
Ben plans to be the first governor of Nevada when a police inspector arrives with a
warrant for his arrest for a murder 20 years ago.
Short Description: While campaigning to be Nevada's governor, Ben receives an arrest warrant

Title: The Spanish Grant
Description: A Spanish heiress arrives to claim land under The Spanish Land Grant and part is on the Ponderosa.
Short Description: A Spanish heiress arrives to claim land on which the Ponderosa sits.

Title: The Trail Gang
Description: Ben and Hoss are herding cattle home when they run across a town that won’t let them through.
Short Description: While herding cattle Ben and Hoss run into trouble

Title: The Savage
Description: Adam comes across a white woman living as an Indian. She nurses him to health when he is wounded and he falls in love.
Short Description: A white woman living as an Indian nurses Adam to health.

Title: The Showdown
Description: The Cartwrights unknowingly hire a bank robber to work at the Ponderosa. Only Joe is suspicious.
Short Description: The Cartwrights unwittingly hire a bank robber at the Ponderosa.
